snippet: Saudi Arabia has injected more than $25 billion into the faltering Egyptian economy in two years, but ties between the two most influential Sunni nations are fraying....
abstract: Egypt votes in favor of Russian-led United Nations resolution on Syrian conflict, prompting economic retaliation from Saudi Arabia; Egypt has had crucial alliance with Saudi Arabian government, which has kept Sunni neighbor afloat financially since Pres Abdel Fattah el-Sisi  took control in 2014.

byline.original: By NOUR YOUSSEF and DIAA HADID
byline.contributor: Nour Youssef reported from Cairo, and Diaa Hadid from Alexandria, Egypt.

lead_paragraph: Saudi Arabia has injected more than $25 billion into the faltering Egyptian economy in two years, but ties between the two most influential Sunni nations are fraying.

headline.main: ‘We Don’t Owe Anyone’: Egypt Jousts With Its Chief Benefactor, Saudi Arabia
headline.print_headline: Egypt Jousts With Chief Benefactor, Saudi Arabia
